Kim Thy (born 1968 in Saigon, Vietnam)[1] is a Canadian writer, whose debut novel Ru won the Governor General's Award for French language fiction at the 2010 Governor General's Awards.[2] Thy spent her early childhood in Vietnam before fleeing with her parents as boat people[1] and settling in the Montreal suburb of Longueuil.[3] She has degrees in law, linguistics and translation from the Universit de Montral.[1] 
